Two Things to Remember While Using @Parameters in TestNG
--------------------------------------------------------

1. In the Test Class
--------------------
- Use the @Parameters annotation.
- The parameter name should match the name in the TestNG XML file.
- The test method must accept the parameter as an argument.

Example:

@Parameters({"browser"})
@Test
public void launchBrowser(String browser)

2. In the TestNG XML File
-------------------------
- Define the parameter using the <parameter> tag.
- Provide the parameter name (key) and its value.

Example:

<parameter name="browser" value="CHROME"></parameter>

Note:
-----
- The parameter name in @Parameters and the name attribute in testng.xml
must be exactly the same.
- The method parameter (String browser) receives the value specified in the XML file.